
Privacy Policy

KrishiSat

Effective Date: August 18, 2024

1. Introduction
Welcome to KrishiSat. We value your privacy and are committed to protecting it. This Privacy Policy explains how we handle user information and outlines our approach to data collection, usage, and protection.

2. Information We Collect
Currently, KrishiSat does not collect any personal data from users. However, in the future, if we decide to collect any information, we will update this Privacy Policy and inform users accordingly.

3. How We Use Your Information
Since we do not collect any user data at this time, we do not use any personal information. If data collection becomes necessary in future updates, we will only use it for the purpose of improving the appâ€™s functionality and services.

4. Sharing Your Information
We do not share any user information with third parties. If we introduce data collection features in the future, we will ensure transparency and notify users about any sharing practices.

5. Data Security
Even though we are not currently collecting any data, we take security seriously. If we collect user information in the future, we will implement security measures to protect it from unauthorized access or misuse.

6. Your Rights and Choices
As we are not collecting data, users do not need to request access, modification, or deletion of personal information at this time.
If data collection begins in the future, we will ensure that users have control over their data, including options to update, delete, or opt out of sharing information.
7. Children's Privacy
KrishiSat is designed for farmers and is not intended for children under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect data from children. If we find that a child has provided personal information, we will take steps to remove it.

8. Changes to This Privacy Policy
Since our app currently does not collect user data, this Privacy Policy reflects our present data handling practices. However, if we start collecting data in the future, we will update this policy and notify users of any changes.

